      "Injured person given full release to return to work with no restrictions"
    ],
    "summary": "On 30-July-2014, while operating an electric pallet jack in the sack room of the Hercules 214 drilling rig, an injured person (IP) sustained a fracture to his left little finger when his hand became caught between a piece of angle iron attached to the wall and the pallet jack handle. The selector switch had become stuck in the reverse position, and as the IP attempted to move the switch back to forward, his hand was caught. The IP had previously experienced the switch becoming stuck but had not reported it to his supervisor or maintenance.",
